{
  "texts": [
    "Steps The number of flow matching (FM) steps governs the granularity of sampling from the learned conditional distribution at each autoregressive step.",
    "While more FM steps can, in principle, yield smoother and more accurate trajectories, they also increase inference cost-even if the MLP used for token decoding remains lightweight.",
    "In fig. 26, we evaluate ENMA's performance as a function of FM steps.",
    "We observe a sharp drop in relative L2 error between 2 and 5 steps, after which the performance plateaus.",
    "Beyond 10 steps, improvements are marginal or even slightly inconsistent."
  ]
}